"Medieval vernacular form of   Matilda .  This form was characteristically Low German (i.e. including medieval Dutch and Flemish). The wife of  William the Conqueror , who bore this name, was the daughter of  Baldwin , Count of Flanders. In Flemish and Dutch the letter <i>-t-</i> was generally lost when it occurred between vowels, giving forms such as <i>Ma(h)auld</i>. <i>Maud</i> or <i>Matilda</i> was also the name of the daughter (  1102–67 ) of  Henry I  of England; she was married early in life to the Holy Roman Emperor  Henry V , and later disputed the throne of England with her cousin  Stephen . In  1128  she married  Geoffrey , Count of Anjou. A medieval chronicler commented, ‘she was a good woman, but she had little bliss with him’. The name <i>Maud</i> became quite common in England in the 19th century, when its popularity was influenced in part by  Tennyson's  poem Maud, published in  1855 , but has not been much used since the early decades of the 20th century."],"variants":[]}],"historicEvents":[{"id":1705187,"age":37,"year":"1215","julianDay":2164830,"title":"Magna Carta","description":"King John of England agreed to a charter of rights called the Magna Carta. The document was originally drafted by the Archbishop of Canterbury to establish peace between King John and a group of rebel barons. The Magna Carta was completed in 1215 and is now considered to be one of the greatest constitutional documents of all time.","url":"https://www.nationalarchives.gov.uk/education/medieval/magna-carta/","urlTitle":"National Archives - Magna Carta","jurisdictionLevel":2},{"id":1705188,"age":46,"year":"1224","julianDay":2168117,"title":"France Declares War on England","description":"France declared war on England as Louis VIII of France attacked Poitou and northern Gascony.","jurisdictionLevel":2}],"lifeSummary":"Maud was born in 1178, in Marston St Lawrence, Northamptonshire, England. She married Richard de Lyons in 1198, in Marston St Lawrence, Northamptonshire, England. They were the parents of at least 1 son. She died in 1224, in Warkworth, Northamptonshire, England, at the age of 46."},"et":{"1178–1224":"1178–1224","1174–1205":"1174–1205","1199–1250":"1199–1250","1205":"1205","1215":"1215","1224":"1224","1178":"1178","1199":"1199","1198":"1198","1174":"1174","1250":"1250","Marston St. Lawrence, Northampton, England":"Marston St Lawrence, Northamptonshire, England","Warkworth, Northampton, England":"Warkworth, Northamptonshire, England","Marston St Lawrence, Northampton, England":"Marston St Lawrence, Northamptonshire, England","Warkworth, Northumberland, England":"Warkworth, Northumberland, England","Manor, Yorkshire, England":"Manor, Yorkshire, England"},"fi":{"1178–1224":"1178–1224","1174–1205":"1174–1205","1199–1250":"1199–1250","1205":"1205","1215":"1215","1224":"1224","1178":"1178","1199":"1199","1198":"1198","1174":"1174","1250":"1250","Marston St. Lawrence, Northampton, England":"Marston St Lawrence, Northamptonshire, England","Warkworth, Northampton, England":"Warkworth, Northamptonshire, England","Marston St Lawrence, Northampton, England":"Marston St Lawrence, Northamptonshire, England","Warkworth, Northumberland, England":"Warkworth, Northumberland, England","Manor, Yorkshire, England":"Manor, Yorkshire, England"},"fr":{"1178–1224":"1178–1224","1174–1205":"1174–1205","1199–1250":"1199–1250","1205":"1205","1215":"1215","1224":"1224","1178":"1178","1199":"1199","1198":"1198","1174":"1174","1250":"1250","Marston St. Lawrence, Northampton, England":"Marston St Lawrence, Northamptonshire, Angleterre","Warkworth, Northampton, England":"Warkworth, Northamptonshire, Angleterre","Marston St Lawrence, Northampton, England":"Marston St Lawrence, Northamptonshire, Angleterre","Warkworth, Northumberland, England":"Warkworth, Northumberland, Angleterre","Manor, Yorkshire, England":"Manor, Everwyck, Angleterre","lifeSummary":"Maud est née en 1178, à Marston St Lawrence, Northamptonshire, Angleterre. Elle a épousé Richard de Lyons